  "summary": "Malicious code in react-next-vite (npm)",
  "details": "The package react-next-vite@1.2.9 is a combosquat of the React, Next.js, and Vite framework names. Its entry point (index.js) spawns a detached background Node.js process that fetches a remote payload from an IPFS URL hosted on the Pinata gateway (bronze-improved-gibbon-411[.]mypinata[.]cloud/ipfs/bafkreigjnxn5vnn34rc5r43ajwwkmk4akqpm4awmq5gdhakgszpeqiffsu) and executes the returned code via the Function constructor, enabling arbitrary remote code execution on the installer's machine. The package has no repository URL and its description is unrelated to its name.",
